      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "Forming Imperfect Subjunctive",
        "content": "Take the ellos form of preterite, remove -ron, add these endings:\n                        → vivieron → vivie- → viviera, vivieras, viviera... = to live",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "-ra, -ras, -ra, -ramos, -ran",
            "english": "Common form"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "hablaron → habla- → hablara, hablaras, hablara...",
            "english": "to speak"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "comieron → comie- → comiera, comieras, comiera...",
            "english": "to eat"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "vivieron → vivie- → viviera, vivieras, viviera...",
            "english": "to live"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "Irregular Imperfect Subjunctives",
        "content": "Use the irregular preterite stem:\n                              \n   ✏️ Exercise: Quería que tú ___ conmigo. (venir)",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "ser/ir → fueron → fuera, fueras, fuera...",
            "english": "were/went"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "tener → tuvieron → tuviera, tuvieras...",
            "english": "had"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "hacer → hicieron → hiciera, hicieras...",
            "english": "did/made"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "poder → pudieron → pudiera, pudieras...",
            "english": "could"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "estar → estuvieron → estuviera, estuvieras...",
            "english": "were"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "Si Clauses (If Clauses)",
        "content": "Three types of conditions:\n                  → Type 3 (Past Unreal): Si hubiera tenido tiempo, habría ido. = If I had had time, I would have gone.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "Type 1 (Real): Si tengo tiempo, voy.",
            "english": "If I have time, I go. (present + present)"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "Type 2 (Hypothetical): Si tuviera tiempo, iría.",
            "english": "If I had time, I would go. (imp subj + conditional)"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "Type 3 (Past Unreal): Si hubiera tenido tiempo, habría ido.",
            "english": "If I had had time, I would have gone."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "Type 2 Si Clause Examples",
        "content": "Hypothetical situations:\n                        \n   ✏️ Exercise: Si ___ más dinero, compraría una casa. (tener)",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "Si fuera rico, viajaría por el mundo.",
            "english": "If I were rich, I would travel the world."
          },
          {
            "spanish": "Si tuviera más tiempo, estudiaría más.",
            "english": "If I had more time, I would study more."
          },
          {
            "spanish": "Si pudiera, te ayudaría.",
            "english": "If I could, I would help you."
          },
          {
            "spanish": "Si estuviera en tu lugar, no lo haría.",
            "english": "If I were in your place, I wouldn't do it."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "Ojalá with Imperfect Subjunctive",
        "content": "Use for unlikely/impossible wishes:\n                  → Ojalá estuvieras aquí. = I wish you were here. (but you're not)",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "Ojalá pudiera ir.",
            "english": "I wish I could go. (but probably can't)"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "Ojalá tuviera más tiempo.",
            "english": "I wish I had more time. (but I don't)"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "Ojalá estuvieras aquí.",
            "english": "I wish you were here. (but you're not)"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
